wafw00f
Web Application Firewall detection tool

Web Application
Description
wafw00f identifies and fingerprints Web Application Firewalls (WAFs). It detects over 100 WAF products and helps plan bypass strategies.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which wafw00f
Install command:

sudo apt install wafw00f
Basic Syntax
wafw00f <url>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
wafw00f http://target.com

Detect WAF	Check for WAF presence	
wafw00f http://target.com -a

Test all WAFs	Thorough detection	
wafw00f http://target.com -v

Verbose output	Detailed results	
wafw00f -l

List supported WAFs	See detectable WAFs	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Run wafw00f against target
2
Note detected WAF type
3
Research WAF bypass techniques
4
Adjust attack payloads accordingly
Understanding the Output
Shows detected WAF product name and version if identifiable.

Important Warnings
•
WAF detection is usually safe
•
Helps plan further testing
•
Some WAFs may block repeated probes
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
